"In today's society, social media is as prevalent in the business world as it is among millennials sharing updates of their weekends and photos of Sunday brunch. While many businesses are adopting social media platforms for networking and sharing insights, it is important to still acknowledge the security risk this may pose. Social media is all about sharing, but this in itself makes it an easy target for attackers to gain usable information. Social media is all about sharing, and this means that many organisations view it as a threat to their information security. However, organisations can learn from the principles of social media to actually increase security. By programmatically sharing information about threats, teams can work together to create a mutual defence and develop stronger protections than those working as lone IT wolves, argues Mav Turner of SolarWinds."
